The paper deals with mathematical programming formulations of graph colouring, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also discusses applications in course timetabling, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.RO). The paper presents empirical results, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
